{{Infobox deity
|NAME = <hiero>N36:N35-M12</hiero><br/>Merencha<br/>''Mr-n-ḫ3''
|NAME-ERWEITERT = {{ill|New Kingdom|ja|新王国|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/New Kingdom|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}
}}

'''Merencha''' (also written '''Mer-en-cha''') is, in [[:en:Egyptian mythology|Egyptian Mythology]], the name of the winding watercourse that, in the land of {{ill|Ta-djeser|ja|タ＝デジェル|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ta-djeser|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, encloses the regions of [[:en:Aaru|Sechet-iaru]], {{ill|Sechet-hetep|ja|セシェト・ヘテプ|de|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sechet-hetep|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, and {{ill|Sechet-tjau|ja|セシェト・チャウ|de|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sechet-tjau|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} located in the [[:en:Duat|Duat]].

Merencha represents, as a likely equivalence of the {{ill|Lake of fire|ja|フレームレイク|lt=Flame|lt_ja=フラメン-|de|Flammensee|es|Lago de fuego|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Lake of fire|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} or {{ill|Knife Lake|ja|ナイフ湖|de|Messersee|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Knife Lake|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, the realm of [[:en:Reincarnation|Reincarnation]] of the [[:en:Solar deity|Sun God]] {{ill|Ra|ja|レ|lt=Ra|lt_ja=レ|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ra|qq=|1=レ|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q9301108}} and of the deceased.

From an inscription accompanying the text passage of the {{ill|Book of the Dead|ja|エジプト死者の書|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Book of the Dead|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, which gave its name to the region of Sechet-Tjau in the {{ill|Late Period (Egypt)|ja|エジプト後期|lt=Late Period|lt_ja=後期|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Late Period (Egypt)|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, it can be inferred that the inhabitants of Sechet-Iaru are capable, like Re at the birthplace of the gods, of performing a [[:en:Sunrise|Sunrise]] and sunset.

After qualification, the deceased can partake in the daily earthly journey of the Sun God; simultaneously, after his reincarnation, he can move freely in the water of Merencha throughout the Duat as well as on [[:en:Earth|Earth]].

== Literature ==
* {{ill|Rolf Krauss|ja|ロルフ・クラウス|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rolf Krauss|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}: ''Astronomical Concepts and Afterlife Beliefs in the Pyramid Texts.'' Harrassowitz, Wiesbaden 1997, ISBN 3-447-03979-5.
* {{ill|Bertha Porter|ja|バーサ・ポーター|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bertha Porter|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}, Ethel W. Burney, {{ill|Rosalind L.B. Moss|ja|ロザリンド・モス|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rosalind L.B. Moss|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}: ''Topographical Bibliography of Ancient Egyptian Hieroglyphic Texts, Reliefs, and Paintings. Vol. 1, The Theban Necropolis. Part 1, Private Tombs.'' Griffith Institute, Oxford 1994, ISBN 0-900416-15-7.

